711945f-a.text:
29th Street, north side, east from 539 West 29th, east of Eleventh Avenue. The houses in the foreground have been condemned by Tenement House Commissioner Langdon Post. In the distance gleams the new Parcel Post Office, which replaced the New York Central
milk sheds.
May 30, 1934.
..  P. L. Sperr.

710613f-a.text:
11th Avenue, west side, north from W. 29th Street. At the left are the remains of a 2-story planing mill. View 2 shows the demolition period of same. This is at the N. W. corner of 29th Street. In the background is a 5-story tenement (No. 319 Eleventh Aenue) at the N. W. corner of 30th Street. This has disappeared in the later view.
Its site would be just behind the foreground aUto.
January 28, 1932
May 12, 1930
P. L. Sperr
